        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 21 at 4:22PM MDT by NWS Cheyenne WY</headline>
        <description>At 421 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Roberts Trailhead Campground, or 11 miles southwest of Chadron,
moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Chadron, Chadron Municipal Airport, Roberts Trailhead Campground,
Chadron State Park, Red Cloud Campground, Dawes County Fairgrounds,
and Chadron State Park Campground.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
